I"±<h3 id="summary">Summary</h3>

<p>For this edition of <em>Beowulf</em>, as translated by J. Lesslie Hall, I had to tackle a layout with three different types of marginalia: line numbers, asides, and footnotes.</p>

<h3 id="description">Description</h3>

<p><img src="../../img/beowulf/1a-title-page.jpg" alt="Title page" />
<em>For the cover, I created a Viking ship on the water using typographical ornaments. These were then echoed in the title page.</em></p>

